benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/block/{blockingId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve blocking state audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: TC01 validates successful retrieval for a valid blockingId (200) with a JSON array of AuditLog objects
Empty Response: TC02 validates 200 with an empty array when no logs exist
Query Parameters: TC08 validates handling of an unexpected query parameter (ignored by API)
Authorization: TC05/TC06 validates 401 for missing/invalid credentials
Response Structure: TC19 validates the JSON schema for AuditLog array
Error Handling: TC03 (404 for non-existent blockingId), TC04 (400/404 for invalid blockingId format), TC07 (503 service unavailable), TC20 (504 timeout) tested
Security Tests: TC11 (SQL injection) and TC12 (XSS) validate input handling and return-safe responses
Performance/Resilience: TC09 (large history) with acceptable response time, TC16 (concurrent requests), TC13 (retry logic), TC20 (timeout) tested
State Variation: TC17 (empty DB) and TC18 (partially populated) scenarios
Regression/Compatibility: TC14 (regression fix) and TC15 (legacy headers) scenarios
gaps: Pagination: no explicit pagination tests for large histories or paging parameters
Rate Limiting: no tests for throttling or rate limiting under high load
Caching Behavior: no tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or If-None-Match semantics
403 Forbidden: no explicit test for insufficient permissions (403) beyond 401 cases
Internal Server Error: no test simulating 500Internal ServerError
CORS/Security headers: no tests around CORS or related header behavior
Boundary/exhaustive UUID testing: TC10 covers min/max UUID but broader UUID boundary variations not fully explored
Granularity of AuditLog validation: TC19 confirms schema; deeper field-level validation could be expanded
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (page/size) if the API supports paging to validate large histories
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under burst traffic
Add caching header tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and If-None-Match workflow
Add dedicated 403 Forbidden test to cover permission-related access control
Add 500 Internal Server Error scenario to validate server-side failure handling
Add CORS/header tests to verify cross-origin access behavior
Expand boundary UUID testing with additional variations (different UUID versions, casing, hyphen placements)
Enhance AuditLog field-level validation with stricter type/required-field checks
